View Conservation Activity

Project Conservation Activity

 

Conservation Activity header contains the following information:

  1. Sub-clasification - the sub-clasification Conservation Activity
  2. State - current Conservation Activity state
  3. Name of the Conservation Activity
  4. Department of the Conservation Activity

Conservation Activity Dashboard Tab

 

Once the Conservation Activity is opened, the Conservation Activity dashboard is displayed. In the Conservation Activity dashboard you can find following information:

  1. Conservation Activity Details - present the Conservation Activity details
  2. Cultural Objects  - the list with all cultural objects related to that Conservation Activity
  3. Ongoing Activities  - displays activities like Projects, Conservation Activities and Tasks related to the Conservation Activity that are in status In Progress
  4. Samples - the list with all Samples related to that Conservation Activity
  5. Documents and media - displays documents and media related to the Conservation Activity
  6. Related persons - the list with all assigned persons to the Conservation Activity like Participant(s), Watchers, etc.
  7. Comments - latest comments on the project and the content created/uploaded in it

To access more detailed information select from following tabs:

  1. Details - to check the Conservation Activity metadata
  2. Cultural Objects - to check the full list with all Cultural Objects related to that Conservation Activity
  3. Documents - to check the full list with all documents related to the Conservation Activity
  4. Media - to check the full list with all images related to the Conservation Activity
  5. Activities - to check the full list with all Activities to the Conservation Activity
  6. System Data - to check system data related to the Conservation Activity
  7. Permissions - to check the applied permissions on the Conservation Activity
  8. Versions - to check the versions on the Conservation Activity
